    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="top">
        <div>
          <h1>Private Instruction at SGCC</h1>
          <p class="sub">
            Coaching is built around one goal, help you improve on the course. We start with a baseline, identify your shot pattern, build a simple plan, and track progress with checkpoints. Juniors move through clear levels. Adults follow a repeatable process that holds up under pressure.
          </p>

          <div class="info-strip" aria-label="Lesson details">
            <div class="chip"><i aria-hidden="true"></i><span><b>Lesson options:</b> 30 minutes, 45 minutes</span></div>
            <div class="chip"><i aria-hidden="true"></i><span><b>Packages:</b> Not offered</span></div>
            <div class="chip"><i aria-hidden="true"></i><span><b>Programs:</b> Seasonal player development blocks</span></div>
            <div class="chip"><i aria-hidden="true"></i><span><b>Location:</b> Springfield Golf & Country Club</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <a class="btn primary" href="contact.html">Book a Lesson</a>
      </div>

      <div class="grid" aria-label="Instruction offerings">
        <!-- Junior -->
        <article class="card">
          <div class="badge"><i></i>Junior Development Model</div>
          <h2>Junior Development Model</h2>
          <p>
            Juniors develop faster when the pathway is clear. Coaching is built around skill benchmarks, on-course testing, and a progression that connects instruction to competition, PGA Junior League, and high school golf.
          </p>

          <div class="cols">
            <div class="mini"><b>Who it’s for</b><span>Ages 6–17. New players through competitive juniors. Families who want structure and a plan.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Expected outcome</b><span>Better contact, more control, stronger scoring skills, and a clear next step in the pathway.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Structured process</b><span>Baseline assessment → level placement (101/202/303) → training blocks → retest and progression.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Focus points</b><span>Ball flight basics, wedge distance control, short game scoring, course routines, competitive readiness.</span></div>
          </div>

          <div class="actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="contact.html">Book Junior Lesson</a>
            <a class="btn" href="academy.html">View SGCC Junior Pathway</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Adult -->
        <article class="card">
          <div class="badge"><i></i>Adult Coaching</div>
          <h2>Adult Coaching</h2>
          <p>
            Most adult golfers do not need more tips. They need a repeatable pattern and a plan that translates to the course. Sessions focus on start line, curvature control, distance control, and simple scoring decisions you can trust.
          </p>

          <div class="cols">
            <div class="mini"><b>Who it’s for</b><span>Beginner to competitive amateur. Players who practice but want real scoring improvement.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Expected outcome</b><span>More predictable ball flight, tighter dispersion, improved wedges, better decisions on the course.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Structured process</b><span>Shot pattern audit → priority fix → drills with purpose → at-home plan → progress checkpoints.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Focus points</b><span>Start line, face-to-path, contact quality, wedge matrix, putting fundamentals, course management.</span></div>
          </div>

          <div class="actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="contact.html">Book Adult Lesson</a>
            <a class="btn" href="contact.html">Ask About Seasonal Programs</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- High Performance -->
        <article class="card">
          <div class="badge"><i></i>High Performance</div>
          <h2>High Performance</h2>
          <p>
            This track is for competitors. We combine testing, structured training blocks, and performance planning. The goal is simple, build a game that holds up in tournaments.
          </p>

          <div class="cols">
            <div class="mini"><b>Who it’s for</b><span>Tournament juniors, high school players, and serious competitors.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Expected outcome</b><span>More distance with control, better scoring under pressure, stronger routines, smarter strategy.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Structured process</b><span>Testing and baseline → training block plan → on-course performance sessions → tournament prep.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Focus points</b><span>Speed development, dispersion control, wedge benchmarks, pressure games, decision rules.</span></div>
          </div>

          <div class="actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="contact.html">Book High Performance</a>
            <a class="btn" href="academy.html">SGCC Competitive Pathway</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- On-Course -->
        <article class="card">
          <div class="badge"><i></i>On-Course Coaching</div>
          <h2>On-Course Coaching</h2>
          <p>
            You can hit it great on the range and still shoot the same scores. On-course coaching builds scoring decisions, targets, and routines in real situations. This is where handicaps drop.
          </p>

          <div class="cols">
            <div class="mini"><b>Who it’s for</b><span>Players stuck at the same scores, tournament players, and adults who want better decision-making.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Expected outcome</b><span>Fewer big numbers, better misses, improved wedge and approach decisions, stronger confidence.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Structured process</b><span>On-course assessment → dispersion-based targets → decision rules → post-round review.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Focus points</b><span>Tee shot planning, approach targets, wedge choices, recovery strategy, reads and pace.</span></div>
          </div>

          <div class="actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="contact.html">Book On-Course</a>
            <a class="btn" href="contact.html">Ask About Availability</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- Seasonal Programs -->
        <article class="card">
          <div class="badge"><i></i>Seasonal Player Development</div>
          <h2>Seasonal Player Development Programs</h2>
          <p>
            No packages. Instead, I run seasonal training blocks for juniors and adults that follow a clear progression, measurable benchmarks, and on-course transfer.
          </p>

          <div class="cols">
            <div class="mini"><b>Who it’s for</b><span>Players who want structure beyond one-off lessons.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Expected outcome</b><span>Clear direction, better practice habits, and visible improvement across the season.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Structured process</b><span>Baseline → training plan → checkpoints → end-of-block review.</span></div>
            <div class="mini"><b>Focus points</b><span>Scoring skills, ball flight, pressure training, course routines.</span></div>
